description:
Add method to retrieve only human-authored notes for context building:

```go
// Note type extension
type Note struct {
    Content   string    `json:"content"`
    Timestamp time.Time `json:"timestamp"`
    Author    string    `json:"author,omitempty"`  // "agent" or "human"
}

// GetHumanNotes returns notes marked as from human
func (c *Client) GetHumanNotes(taskID string) ([]Note, error) {
    notes, err := c.GetNotes(taskID)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }

    var humanNotes []Note
    for _, n := range notes {
        if n.Author == "human" {
            humanNotes = append(humanNotes, n)
        }
    }
    return humanNotes, nil
}
```

This is used by the engine to build context when a task returns from human.

Acceptance criteria:
- [ ] Note struct has Author field
- [ ] GetHumanNotes filters correctly
- [ ] Returns empty slice if no human notes
- [ ] Works with existing notes (treats as agent by default)
